commit.message: Generated ldg/osmesa.h was missing a } for __cplusplus

Fix Fcntl(FUTIME) in hostfs

The conversion from dos-style timestamps to unix was already done by
the kernel
Add ar-lib from automake to .giignore
stripex: preserve filemode of original
Build optimized nfeth-config

USBhost: Correct bulk transfer return value wrong assumption

Bulk transfer return value doesn't contain number of bytes transferred.
USBhost: Set port enable status bit after set feature request
USBhost: Place the virtual port in an enabled state after reset

USBhost: Translate ATARI device index 0 to the proper host device index

From the ATARI side unconfigured USB devices have index number 0, we need
to translate it to the right index given by the host.
Update stripex tool to support new MiNT+ELF program format

Fix a bug in DEV_SELECT callback for hostfs

The return code is the number of bytes ready to be read/written. A
return code of 0 causes Fselect to hang indefinitely when used without
a timeout.
Update glibc wrapper to include new symbols from glibc 2.38
Use `sizeof` where possible
Disable warnings about implicit 64-bit to 32-bit conversion
Fix warnings related to `sprintf` usage
Updating information about building a notarized package.
Ensure executable is not updated if it not necessary
Disable "Hardened Runtime" in Debug builds to allow debugging
Added section about how notarization can be done
Add "codesign" after disk image generation with artificial disk image bundle ID
Enforce "Manual" code signing style
Add flag to generate "secure timestamp" (required for notarization)
Do not inject base entitlements in "Release" builds (=target "Packaging") to allow notarization.
Add individual bundle identifiers to each app target
Make sure "Create Diskimage" script is always run
Enable "Hardened Runtime" on all targets and add empty entitlements file (required in the future for signed distributable builds)
Reveal generated DMG in Finder

corrects "Reorganize tos patches for 4.04" commit from 2018/9/21, fixes #45

GitHub issue "Aranym fails to boot hard disk driver from big drive images"

Revert "Implement Timer-A emulation (delay-mode only)."

This reverts commit dc693d130c76cc945269c64c1467f9c6eb45e670.

configure.ac: fix bashisms

configure scripts need to be runnable with a POSIX-compliant /bin/sh.

On many (but not all!) systems, /bin/sh is provided by Bash, so errors
like this aren't spotted. Notably Debian defaults to /bin/sh provided
by dash which doesn't tolerate such bashisms as '=='.

This retains compatibility with bash.
